1
00:01:53,939 --> 00:01:54,500
Dad,

2
00:01:55,099 --> 00:01:57,459
the company leadership asked me to formally notify you

3
00:01:57,459 --> 00:02:00,260
to process your retirement procedures.

4
00:02:02,859 --> 00:02:03,980
Oh my god.

5
00:02:03,980 --> 00:02:05,340
I finally said it.

6
00:02:05,340 --> 00:02:07,120
I conquered myself.

7
00:02:11,740 --> 00:02:12,699
What did you say?

8
00:02:13,699 --> 00:02:14,539
You didn't hear?

9
00:02:15,180 --> 00:02:15,939
This is killing me.

10
00:02:15,939 --> 00:02:17,500
I have to say it again?

11
00:02:18,300 --> 00:02:19,099
Dad,

12
00:02:19,659 --> 00:02:23,460
the company leadership asked me to formally notify you

13
00:02:23,539 --> 00:02:25,460
to process your retirement.

14
00:02:25,460 --> 00:02:26,460
I heard you.

15
00:02:30,060 --> 00:02:31,419
Were those their exact words,

16
00:02:32,219 --> 00:02:33,780
or is that your summary?

17
00:02:34,620 --> 00:02:36,219
Mr. Ma's exact words, Dad.

18
00:02:36,219 --> 00:02:37,099
For such a big matter,

19
00:02:37,099 --> 00:02:39,139
how could I just summarize it?

20
00:02:39,659 --> 00:02:40,819
They've been rushing me for a while.

21
00:02:40,819 --> 00:02:42,699
I've been under huge pressure too.

22
00:02:44,539 --> 00:02:45,340
What?

23
00:02:46,879 --> 00:02:47,219
Who?

24
00:02:47,219 --> 00:02:47,939
Maotai.

25
00:02:48,939 --> 00:02:50,460
Bring me that Maotai.

26
00:02:51,340 --> 00:02:52,139
Right.

27
00:02:52,180 --> 00:02:53,419
Hurry up.

28
00:02:53,419 --> 00:02:54,740
Can't you even handle this?

29
00:02:54,740 --> 00:02:55,659
You really are...

30
00:02:56,099 --> 00:02:56,580
Dad,

31
00:02:56,580 --> 00:02:58,340
don't take it to heart.

32
00:03:04,819 --> 00:03:05,620
This...

33
00:03:06,139 --> 00:03:07,219
there's not much food left.

34
00:03:08,520 --> 00:03:09,319
It's fine.

35
00:03:09,500 --> 00:03:11,599
I'll fry two more eggs to go with the drink.

36
00:03:13,280 --> 00:03:13,919
Don't bother.

37
00:03:13,919 --> 00:03:14,819
Just sit here.

38
00:03:16,620 --> 00:03:18,580
Listen to me tell you from the beginning.

39
00:03:18,719 --> 00:03:19,699
From the beginning?

40
00:03:21,180 --> 00:03:22,560
Let's not go too far back.

41
00:03:23,860 --> 00:03:25,539
Just start from when the company launched.

42
00:03:26,439 --> 00:03:27,520
That's not far back?

43
00:03:27,520 --> 00:03:28,759
It's been thirty years.

44
00:03:29,439 --> 00:03:30,400
Back then,

45
00:03:30,900 --> 00:03:31,979
running for permits,

46
00:03:31,979 --> 00:03:33,060
getting approvals,

47
00:03:33,740 --> 00:03:35,699
finding connections and pulling strings.

48
00:03:36,219 --> 00:03:37,580
To take a company,

49
00:03:37,620 --> 00:03:40,479
build it from scratch,

50
00:03:42,819 --> 00:03:43,460
who did we rely on?

51
00:03:44,139 --> 00:03:44,800
Relied on...

52
00:03:46,539 --> 00:03:47,199
You.

53
00:03:50,139 --> 00:03:52,599
When the company just took shape,

54
00:03:52,900 --> 00:03:54,979
we hit the financial crisis.

55
00:03:55,620 --> 00:03:57,099
Monetary tightening.

56
00:03:57,740 --> 00:04:00,219
So many companies collapsed.

57
00:04:00,539 --> 00:04:02,000
We, a private enterprise,

58
00:04:02,139 --> 00:04:03,800
how did we survive?

59
00:04:05,340 --> 00:04:07,060
Financing and loans,

60
00:04:07,259 --> 00:04:09,020
increasing income and cutting costs,

61
00:04:09,180 --> 00:04:11,180
braving the storm.

62
00:04:12,860 --> 00:04:13,780
Who did we rely on then?

63
00:04:14,259 --> 00:04:15,740
Still relied on you.

64
00:04:16,779 --> 00:04:18,019
And later,

65
00:04:18,819 --> 00:04:20,459
the company developed,

66
00:04:20,899 --> 00:04:22,699
financing, venture capital...

67
00:04:23,579 --> 00:04:24,379
Dad,

68
00:04:24,699 --> 00:04:26,819
I know about the financing part.

69
00:04:27,339 --> 00:04:29,139
That was all thanks to Mr. Ma.

70
00:04:29,139 --> 00:04:32,139
That batch of young executives who studied finance.

71
00:04:32,139 --> 00:04:34,819
What young executives?

72
00:04:35,379 --> 00:04:36,500
What do they know?

73
00:04:36,860 --> 00:04:37,579
Don't get angry.

74
00:04:37,579 --> 00:04:39,060
Without me clearing the way through mountains,

75
00:04:39,060 --> 00:04:40,180
building bridges over water,

76
00:04:40,220 --> 00:04:41,259
paving the way for them,

77
00:04:41,259 --> 00:04:42,420
teaching them experience,

78
00:04:42,500 --> 00:04:43,819
could they have succeeded?

79
00:04:43,819 --> 00:04:44,019
Right.

80
00:04:44,019 --> 00:04:45,220
Would they be where they are today?

81
00:04:45,220 --> 00:04:45,980
I understand.

82
00:04:45,980 --> 00:04:46,660
Speak up.

83
00:04:46,660 --> 00:04:48,060
I... I... I misspoke.

84
00:04:48,060 --> 00:04:48,839
I misspoke.

85
00:04:48,839 --> 00:04:49,939
I said it wrong.

86
00:04:49,939 --> 00:04:50,699
Wrong.

87
00:04:50,699 --> 00:04:52,259
If it's wrong, it must be corrected.

88
00:04:52,259 --> 00:04:52,540
Correct it.

89
00:04:52,540 --> 00:04:54,860
And not casting aside the hound,

90
00:04:54,860 --> 00:04:56,180
hiding the bow,

91
00:04:56,220 --> 00:04:57,699
burning the bridge,

92
00:04:57,740 --> 00:04:58,819
or killing the donkey.

93
00:04:58,819 --> 00:04:59,220
Right.

94
00:04:59,220 --> 00:05:00,060
Who is the donkey?

95
00:05:00,060 --> 00:05:00,360
Right.

96
00:05:00,360 --> 00:05:01,620
Who is the donkey?

97
00:05:01,740 --> 00:05:02,959
Who is the donkey?

98
00:05:03,100 --> 00:05:03,980
I... I am the donkey.

99
00:05:03,980 --> 00:05:04,779
I am the donkey.

100
00:05:04,779 --> 00:05:05,660
I'm not a donkey either!

101
00:05:05,660 --> 00:05:06,259
Dad,

102
00:05:06,259 --> 00:05:06,779
this...

103
00:05:06,899 --> 00:05:07,860
about this matter,

104
00:05:07,860 --> 00:05:08,579
I think,

105
00:05:08,579 --> 00:05:10,939
if anyone is to blame, it's that Mr. Ma.

106
00:05:13,420 --> 00:05:15,019
That Little Ma.

107
00:05:16,660 --> 00:05:17,100
He...

108
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:19,139
If he wasn't

109
00:05:19,300 --> 00:05:21,139
Chairman Jia's son-in-law,

110
00:05:21,220 --> 00:05:22,420
would he be here today?

111
00:05:23,139 --> 00:05:23,819
No.

112
00:05:25,620 --> 00:05:27,540
To your face, it's "yes, yes, yes",

113
00:05:28,379 --> 00:05:30,220
then he kicks you from below.

114
00:05:31,620 --> 00:05:33,399
Calls you "brother" to your face,

115
00:05:33,959 --> 00:05:35,680
then pulls a weapon when he turns around.

116
00:05:36,279 --> 00:05:38,079
Praises you high to your face,

117
00:05:38,560 --> 00:05:40,579
stabs you in the back.

118
00:05:40,740 --> 00:05:41,540
Dad,

119
00:05:41,740 --> 00:05:42,480
this Mr. Ma,

120
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:44,740
isn't as bad as you say.

121
00:05:44,939 --> 00:05:45,699
Besides,

122
00:05:45,699 --> 00:05:46,720
no matter how you put it,

123
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:48,540
it is the Jia family's enterprise now.

124
00:05:48,540 --> 00:05:49,300
Isn't it?

125
00:05:49,300 --> 00:05:51,500
Back then, retiring at the age limit,

126
00:05:51,500 --> 00:05:53,860
you raised your hand to agree yourself.

127
00:05:54,620 --> 00:05:55,420
Raised my hand?

128
00:05:57,379 --> 00:05:59,420
Wasn't I doing that to get Old Zheng

129
00:05:59,420 --> 00:06:01,420
and Old Fu out of there?

130
00:06:01,779 --> 00:06:02,660
Who would have thought

131
00:06:03,459 --> 00:06:05,819
it would be my turn so soon.

132
00:06:15,540 --> 00:06:16,540
The top priority right now

133
00:06:16,540 --> 00:06:18,259
is finding something for Dad to do, I think.

134
00:06:18,300 --> 00:06:19,660
A person can't stay idle all the time.

135
00:06:19,660 --> 00:06:21,220
Idleness leads to all sorts of problems.

136
00:06:21,779 --> 00:06:23,259
What should he do?

137
00:06:23,699 --> 00:06:27,220
In the hearts of red teenagers

138
00:06:27,220 --> 00:06:31,040
Grow red wings

139
00:06:31,740 --> 00:06:33,540
Be prepared

140
00:06:33,660 --> 00:06:36,920
Always be prepared

141
00:06:37,540 --> 00:06:38,980
What is all that?

142
00:06:39,019 --> 00:06:40,120
At his age,

143
00:06:40,120 --> 00:06:41,579
you want him to sing at a bar?

144
00:06:41,939 --> 00:06:42,740
What's wrong with that?

145
00:06:43,420 --> 00:06:45,620
At the Jin Jiang Hotel in Shanghai,

146
00:06:45,660 --> 00:06:47,420
that jazz bar there,

147
00:06:47,779 --> 00:06:48,779
the singers and musicians

148
00:06:48,779 --> 00:06:49,899
are all old men.

149
00:06:49,899 --> 00:06:51,500
They don't even want young people.

150
00:06:51,899 --> 00:06:53,379
Give me a break.

151
00:06:53,420 --> 00:06:54,779
What a lousy idea.

152
00:06:54,980 --> 00:06:55,800
Really.

153
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:57,060
It's really trendy now.

154
00:06:57,060 --> 00:06:57,920
Let me tell you,

155
00:06:58,899 --> 00:07:01,620
a few close friends get together,

156
00:07:01,660 --> 00:07:03,180
form a small band,

157
00:07:03,740 --> 00:07:04,620
rehearse when free,

158
00:07:04,620 --> 00:07:05,540
perform when busy.

159
00:07:05,899 --> 00:07:07,339
A few of my close classmates,

160
00:07:07,339 --> 00:07:08,300
that's exactly what we do.

161
00:07:08,300 --> 00:07:09,459
Classmates?

162
00:07:11,540 --> 00:07:12,139
Wu Yuntang.

163
00:07:12,139 --> 00:07:13,579
If you hadn't mentioned it, I would've forgotten.

164
00:07:13,779 --> 00:07:16,019
What's going on with that female classmate of yours?

165
00:07:17,220 --> 00:07:18,420
What? What female classmate?

166
00:07:24,060 --> 00:07:25,220
I am willing

167
00:07:27,459 --> 00:07:29,019
to be a cloud,

168
00:07:31,579 --> 00:07:34,519
a gray tattered flag,

169
00:07:36,779 --> 00:07:39,439
in the vast sky,

170
00:07:41,379 --> 00:07:42,899
lazily

171
00:07:44,060 --> 00:07:47,379
floating to and fro.

172
00:07:49,540 --> 00:07:51,420
As long as my lover...

173
00:08:21,579 --> 00:08:22,379
Wifey,

174
00:08:23,379 --> 00:08:24,500
taste this.

175
00:08:25,779 --> 00:08:27,139
Braised fried egg.

176
00:08:28,899 --> 00:08:29,699
Honey

177
00:08:30,139 --> 00:08:30,819
Do you want me to

178
00:08:30,819 --> 00:08:32,899
make you a few side dishes

179
00:08:34,379 --> 00:08:35,179
Honey

180
00:08:36,100 --> 00:08:37,779
The fried egg won't be good cold

181
00:08:37,779 --> 00:08:38,820
You gotta eat it hot

182
00:08:38,820 --> 00:08:39,980
I got it

183
00:08:40,980 --> 00:08:41,779
Honey

184
00:08:42,740 --> 00:08:44,860
You still look unhappy

185
00:08:45,299 --> 00:08:47,419
I explained it all clearly

186
00:08:47,500 --> 00:08:50,620
She's just a regular bestie

187
00:08:50,740 --> 00:08:51,620
So annoying

188
00:08:51,620 --> 00:08:53,620
Mention that bestie again and I'll snap

189
00:08:53,620 --> 00:08:54,419
No

190
00:08:54,419 --> 00:08:56,899
I'm figuring out how to tell Dad

191
00:08:58,059 --> 00:08:58,860
Morning

192
00:08:59,139 --> 00:08:59,899
Dad

193
00:08:59,899 --> 00:09:00,419
Dad

194
00:09:00,419 --> 00:09:01,539
What do you want to tell me?

195
00:09:02,139 --> 00:09:03,700
You slept pretty well last night, huh?

196
00:09:03,700 --> 00:09:04,340
Good

197
00:09:04,820 --> 00:09:05,740
Why wouldn't it be?

198
00:09:05,740 --> 00:09:06,179
Right

199
00:09:06,179 --> 00:09:07,419
Slept with a clear conscience

200
00:09:07,460 --> 00:09:08,440
Right

201
00:09:09,419 --> 00:09:10,220
And...

202
00:09:11,340 --> 00:09:13,340
while I was half-asleep

203
00:09:13,980 --> 00:09:16,620
I made a major decision

204
00:09:17,100 --> 00:09:18,100
What decision?

205
00:09:19,059 --> 00:09:19,860
I decided

206
00:09:20,500 --> 00:09:21,980
to go to Yangliu Xincheng

207
00:09:22,179 --> 00:09:23,659
and spend the rest of my life

208
00:09:23,860 --> 00:09:24,580
Retire

209
00:09:24,580 --> 00:09:25,539
Do it properly

210
00:09:26,259 --> 00:09:27,620
Yangliu Xin...

211
00:09:28,259 --> 00:09:29,700
That retirement community

212
00:09:30,340 --> 00:09:31,860
Dad, you can't go there

213
00:09:31,940 --> 00:09:33,299
Such a major decision

214
00:09:33,299 --> 00:09:34,740
how could you, while half-asleep,

215
00:09:34,740 --> 00:09:35,600
just make a decision?

216
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:36,860
You can't go

217
00:09:36,860 --> 00:09:37,779
Why can't I?

218
00:09:37,779 --> 00:09:38,460
Because you...

219
00:09:38,460 --> 00:09:39,379
Because...

220
00:09:39,379 --> 00:09:39,799
Be...

221
00:09:40,120 --> 00:09:40,539
...cause...

222
00:09:40,940 --> 00:09:42,220
Say something, will you?

223
00:09:42,379 --> 00:09:43,039
Right

224
00:09:43,039 --> 00:09:44,100
Because

225
00:09:44,779 --> 00:09:47,460
many important things need you

226
00:09:47,639 --> 00:09:48,740
What a joke

227
00:09:50,100 --> 00:09:51,740
Then why make me retire with one sentence?

228
00:09:51,980 --> 00:09:52,779
Why?

229
00:09:53,019 --> 00:09:55,379
You're not fully retired, Dad

230
00:09:55,860 --> 00:09:57,460
Mr. Ma meant that

231
00:09:57,820 --> 00:10:01,659
he wants you to lead our magazine

232
00:10:03,299 --> 00:10:05,059
Even bigger joke

233
00:10:05,259 --> 00:10:06,899
An internal company newsletter

234
00:10:07,059 --> 00:10:08,299
Editing and reporting combined

235
00:10:08,419 --> 00:10:10,299
The whole staff is just one person

236
00:10:10,419 --> 00:10:11,259
Who do I lead?

237
00:10:11,720 --> 00:10:12,899
Ex-exactly

238
00:10:12,899 --> 00:10:14,259
We're really not going

239
00:10:14,259 --> 00:10:16,620
Dad has been busy for most of his life

240
00:10:16,620 --> 00:10:18,059
Why worry about them?

241
00:10:18,059 --> 00:10:18,879
Not going

242
00:10:18,879 --> 00:10:19,820
Dad, let's not go

243
00:10:20,100 --> 00:10:21,700
You finally stepped down

244
00:10:22,220 --> 00:10:23,659
I want to use this chance

245
00:10:24,220 --> 00:10:25,179
to practice painting

246
00:10:26,259 --> 00:10:27,259
do calligraphy

247
00:10:27,899 --> 00:10:29,539
learn opera, sing songs

248
00:10:29,539 --> 00:10:30,059
Right

249
00:10:30,059 --> 00:10:30,659
Dad

250
00:10:30,659 --> 00:10:32,100
I've always wanted to ask you

251
00:10:32,179 --> 00:10:34,940
how do you sing so well?

252
00:10:34,940 --> 00:10:35,740
And you

253
00:10:35,740 --> 00:10:37,340
never went to music school

254
00:10:37,500 --> 00:10:39,379
never joined a professional troupe

255
00:10:39,820 --> 00:10:41,220
How come compared to that

256
00:10:41,259 --> 00:10:43,259
Bocelli, you're not bad?

257
00:10:44,700 --> 00:10:45,500
Right

258
00:10:45,820 --> 00:10:46,659
Not bad at all

259
00:10:48,419 --> 00:10:49,220
Daughter

260
00:10:49,460 --> 00:10:51,039
You say I don't know this Bao guy

261
00:10:51,460 --> 00:10:52,620
But you don't know

262
00:10:52,620 --> 00:10:53,379
Back in the day, Dad

263
00:10:53,379 --> 00:10:55,620
Was the lead singer of the Children's Palace Choir

264
00:10:55,659 --> 00:10:56,740
We only had about three hundred people back then

265
00:10:56,740 --> 00:10:57,580
Dad

266
00:10:57,580 --> 00:10:58,299
I think

267
00:10:58,299 --> 00:10:58,799
You

268
00:10:59,059 --> 00:11:00,820
Have no right

269
00:11:00,820 --> 00:11:03,059
To squander your artistic talent anymore

270
00:11:03,860 --> 00:11:06,539
In the past, you were tied up with official duties

271
00:11:06,659 --> 00:11:08,120
Busy with mundane affairs

272
00:11:08,419 --> 00:11:09,740
Now you are free

273
00:11:09,740 --> 00:11:11,460
You can totally compete with

274
00:11:11,620 --> 00:11:12,539
Liao Changyong

275
00:11:12,620 --> 00:11:14,539
And Yan Weiwen

276
00:11:14,899 --> 00:11:15,539
By the way

277
00:11:15,539 --> 00:11:18,019
Is your style Folk or Bel Canto?

278
00:11:18,100 --> 00:11:18,700
I...

279
00:11:20,779 --> 00:11:22,240
I guess mine is the children's choir style

280
00:11:26,179 --> 00:11:29,299
One, two, three, go

281
00:11:29,759 --> 00:11:36,220
Nothing is more beautiful than the sunset red

282
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:42,840
Warm and leisurely

283
00:11:43,399 --> 00:11:49,820
The sunset is a late-blooming flower

284
00:11:50,120 --> 00:11:56,139
The sunset is aged wine

285
00:11:56,500 --> 00:11:57,539
Stop

286
00:11:58,519 --> 00:11:59,919
Something isn't right

287
00:11:59,919 --> 00:12:01,320
Come on, keep singing

288
00:12:01,320 --> 00:12:02,480
Sing again

289
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:03,720
Come on, continue

290
00:12:03,759 --> 00:12:09,600
The sunset is belated love

291
00:12:09,919 --> 00:12:16,059
The sunset is unending affection

292
00:12:16,639 --> 00:12:22,120
How much love

293
00:12:22,120 --> 00:12:23,080
Stop

294
00:12:24,960 --> 00:12:26,159
It sounds so awkward

295
00:12:27,679 --> 00:12:28,600
Come on, tenors

296
00:12:28,759 --> 00:12:30,279
You five, try it once

297
00:12:30,279 --> 00:12:31,220
One, two, three, go

298
00:12:31,220 --> 00:12:31,639
Come on

